1035
01:44:20,069 --> 01:44:23,290
Chief Buckley is a member of the Human Rights Commission.

1036
01:44:24,651 --> 01:44:30,033
We had many meetings, monthly and in between, and many email exchanges.

1037
01:44:30,714 --> 01:44:37,877
I have never heard one word that this policy was a problem for the police, not once.

1038
01:44:38,737 --> 01:44:39,518
And I have

1039
01:44:40,714 --> 01:44:53,977
been watching all the communications from the police, and I have never seen any problem with the administration of this policy.

1040
01:44:55,177 --> 01:45:00,158
I fully support the codification of this, and I thank the city council for moving on this.

1041
01:45:00,678 --> 01:45:01,038
Thank you.

1042
01:45:02,999 --> 01:45:03,439
Thank you.

1043
01:45:04,299 --> 01:45:05,499
We'll go to the podium.

1044
01:45:05,519 --> 01:45:08,600
Name and address for the record, please.

1045
01:45:09,485 --> 01:45:10,626
And you'll have three minutes.

1046
01:45:11,827 --> 01:45:13,928
Victor Alejo, 40 Robinson Road.

1047
01:45:14,929 --> 01:45:18,051
So I'm here tonight to speak, again, against this ordinance.

1048
01:45:18,912 --> 01:45:25,617
Although I do see some changes were made, like getting rid of effectively all of the section on enforcement.

1049
01:45:26,537 --> 01:45:28,299
I still don't believe this ordinance is legal.

1050
01:45:28,439 --> 01:45:34,243
And I think sooner or later, a court, probably the United States Supreme Court, to be honest with you,

1051
01:45:34,724 --> 01:45:38,189
is going to strike it down, and it's like, as unconstitutional.

1052
01:45:39,150 --> 01:45:51,766
The reason I believe this is, like I said the last time I was up here, is that it really does try to put local and state laws above federal law, which the Constitution prevents, as much as the city council might not like.

1053
01:45:52,625 --> 01:46:00,367
That federal law says being in the United States unlawfully is against the law and could subject a person to removal, deportation proceedings.

1054
01:46:01,087 --> 01:46:01,807
This is the law.

1055
01:46:02,447 --> 01:46:06,608
If you don't like it, petition your representatives in Congress to do something about it.

1056
01:46:07,008 --> 01:46:07,848
That's the remedy.

1057
01:46:08,568 --> 01:46:16,410
The remedy is not to do what the city council is doing or attempting to do, which is act far beyond its legal authority.

1058
01:46:17,570 --> 01:46:22,351
I spoke the last time about some practical reasons why I think this ordinance is bad policy.

1059
01:46:22,824 --> 01:46:23,845
And I'll just reiterate them.

1060
01:46:24,525 --> 01:46:33,711
I think even with the tempered language, the ordinance still does handicap to a significant degree, the police department's ability to do its job, which is to keep the community safe.

1061
01:46:34,231 --> 01:46:41,536
And I just point as two examples here, look at 103D, talks about the police department not being able to initiate investigations.

1062
01:46:42,435 --> 01:46:46,997
look at 103E, which limits the department's ability to make arrests.

1063
01:46:47,717 --> 01:46:50,538
These are two fundamental functions of what police departments do.

1064
01:46:50,578 --> 01:46:55,180
They investigate, and they make arrests of people who are not obeying the law.

1065
01:46:55,260 --> 01:47:01,863
So us telling us, essentially, police departments don't do what you're designed to do, what you're supposed to be doing.

1066
01:47:02,683 --> 01:47:09,986
And again, I understand there's tremendous intent tonight to approve this ordinance, but I would seriously just ask you to at least wait until the U.S.

1067
01:47:10,006 --> 01:47:21,850
Supreme Court weighs in on this, because I'm telling you, there's going to be a case about this, and it's going to strike this down, and the city's going to be embarrassed, and it's going to show that Medford's leaders don't really understand the concept of limited government.

1068
01:47:22,390 --> 01:47:23,451
That's what I have to say tonight.

1069
01:47:23,731 --> 01:47:24,431
Thank you for listening.

1070
01:47:24,451 --> 01:47:26,212
Thank you.

1071
01:47:27,492 --> 01:47:29,313
No one on Zoom, so we'll remain at the podium.

1072
01:47:30,640 --> 01:47:31,821
name and address for the record.

1073
01:47:31,861 --> 01:47:32,801
You have three minutes.

1074
01:47:34,021 --> 01:47:34,402
Good evening.

1075
01:47:34,442 --> 01:47:37,163
Thank you so much, Laura Rotolo, 14 Rita Drive.

1076
01:47:37,183 --> 01:47:44,605
I'm also here on behalf of the American Civil Liberties Union of Massachusetts and our thousands of members and supporters here in Medford.

1077
01:47:45,286 --> 01:47:49,667
Very quickly to thank the city council for this third reading of this important ordinance.

1078
01:47:49,848 --> 01:47:52,949
I too am an immigrant who's been living in Medford for about 30

1079
01:47:54,229 --> 01:47:59,372
I'm very proud to call this place my home and to support other immigrants here.

1080
01:47:59,752 --> 01:48:15,160
Just to address some of the questions posed earlier about the legality of this, of course, Medford is one of dozens of cities and towns in Massachusetts to pass a similar ordinance, including the cities of Boston, Cambridge, Somerville, very recently.

1081
01:48:15,720 --> 01:48:21,225
It has been looked at by the council for the city for legality.

1082
01:48:21,926 --> 01:48:34,018
These issues have been litigated across the country and there is nothing in here that limits the police's ability to carry forth a lawful arrest or its lawful duties as the police department.

1083
01:48:35,339 --> 01:48:38,301
Again, many cities and towns have passed very similar language.

1084
01:48:38,641 --> 01:48:41,703
We look forward to Medford being the next city to do so.

1085
01:48:42,764 --> 01:48:47,968
And again, it just focuses on this voluntary collaboration with immigration authorities.

1086
01:48:48,508 --> 01:48:49,289
And I thank you again.

1087
01:48:51,210 --> 01:48:51,710
Thank you.

1088
01:48:51,730 --> 01:48:53,592
We'll go back to Zoom.

1089
01:48:54,372 --> 01:48:57,895
Muneer Jumanis, I'll ask you to unmute and you'll have three minutes.

1090
01:48:57,995 --> 01:49:00,497
Name and address for the record, please.

1091
01:49:00,997 --> 01:49:02,098
I'm Muneer Jumanis.

1092
01:49:02,298 --> 01:49:02,998
I live at 370 Road.

1093
01:49:04,865 --> 01:49:20,077
And I'm, once again, congratulating the city council for taking this measure up and highly recommend a yes vote as was mentioned previously.

1094
01:49:21,999 --> 01:49:28,544
We had discussions about these policies for several years.

1095
01:49:28,784 --> 01:49:30,465
I was chair of the Human Rights Commission.

1096
01:49:31,026 --> 01:49:33,568
Chief Buckley is part of the Human Rights Commission.

1097
01:49:34,529 --> 01:49:41,613
And there was never any issues with the proposed policies.

1098
01:49:42,293 --> 01:49:51,438
And similarly, I would say, since this ordinance simply codifies these policies, I don't expect that there will be any change.

1099
01:49:52,618 --> 01:49:55,260
And I'm an immigrant myself.

1100
01:49:56,120 --> 01:50:01,903
Some immigrants have faced severe bias.

1101
01:50:03,204 --> 01:50:03,924
Others have not.

1102
01:50:04,730 --> 01:50:13,957
That does not mean that the experience of one immigrant who has not faced any such bias says it all.

1103
01:50:14,577 --> 01:50:18,940
So once again, I urge the council to approve this policy.

1104
01:50:19,200 --> 01:50:20,801
Thank you for your attention.

1105
01:50:23,804 --> 01:50:24,324
Thank you.

1106
01:50:24,344 --> 01:50:27,646
We'll stay on Zoom.

