1200
01:57:16,932 --> 01:57:18,613
I haven't been living in Medford very long.

1201
01:57:19,513 --> 01:57:21,754
Before this, I lived in Texas for a long time.

1202
01:57:21,834 --> 01:57:25,555
I was in Texas during the Trump administration previously.

1203
01:57:27,676 --> 01:57:28,877
I lived in North Austin.

1204
01:57:28,897 --> 01:57:32,800
It was a very robust neighborhood, a wonderful community.

1205
01:57:33,280 --> 01:57:34,881
I was a high school physics teacher there.

1206
01:57:35,642 --> 01:57:40,485
And during the crackdowns with ICE, it tore our community apart.

1207
01:57:40,705 --> 01:57:41,786
It was horrifying.

1208
01:57:42,826 --> 01:57:49,411
People would disappear on their way home from the grocery store, or people just wouldn't show up at work.

1209
01:57:50,071 --> 01:57:53,854
I had students who were afraid that they weren't going to be at school the next day.

1210
01:57:55,177 --> 01:57:56,441
It didn't feel safe.

1211
01:57:57,183 --> 01:58:00,291
It didn't feel like I was living in a free country.

1212
01:58:00,832 --> 01:58:01,614
It was scary.

1213
01:58:03,579 --> 01:58:10,483
And honestly, living up here in New England now, I feel like I'm in a slightly more civilized place.

1214
01:58:11,423 --> 01:58:17,127
And I was so, so excited to hear about this ordinance, to hear about the work that's already been done.

1215
01:58:17,987 --> 01:58:29,094
And I'm in huge, huge support of, you know, just codifying this and making it real, because I don't want to live in a neighborhood like that again, because it was awful.

1216
01:58:29,794 --> 01:58:32,118
and I don't want that to happen to our community here.

1217
01:58:32,438 --> 01:58:34,161
Thank you very much for the work that you're doing.

1218
01:58:36,164 --> 01:58:36,725
Thank you.

